				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How many songs can a non bard have?<a name="63810"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 23 04 11:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Depends what slot they go in.  You can only have 6 temporary buffs -- the &quot;song&quot; window.  That could be 6 bard songs or it could be 5 bard songs and a cleric Aura, which also lives in that temporary box.  A couple of bard songs go in the long term buff box like Selo's Accelerating Chorus.  So the answer is 6 in the temp box and however many you can squeeze into the long term box.  If we're talking actual sun songs and not click effects, I would bet 6 songs plus Selo's is the limit and that won't be up for long.  Of course with more than one bard, you can fill that 6 songs easily.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
