			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How many songs can a non bard have?<a name="63812"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 23 04 11:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The song buff box has six buff slots. When those are filled, bard songs go into the spell buff box. This should NOT ever be an issue. The only time the spell buff box is going to be full is at a raid or in the short time just after a raid. And the only time when the song buff box will be filled is when you have more than one bard in the group. I can't ever see a circumstance when at a raid you would have two bards in a group. 
<br />

<br />
Any bard who is twisting more than 3 or 4 songs is using parlor tricks that may impress folks who don't know the bard class but won't impress other bards. I have gotten 6 to 8 songs up before, but they were not songs that were helping the group. It was just for kicks and grins. I have a bagged insta cast BOH that you can twist with selos (one sec cast off of ornate legs), song of sustenance (lasts way longer than most songs), warsong (lasts extra tick I think), Kattas (lasts an extra tick I think) and some standard stuff. Add it all up and you can twist 6 to 8 songs for an instant, but it is a joke to do it.
<br />

<br />
Drumm
<br />
67 Bard
<br />
Torv Server</span></td>
