			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Thanks for all the responses, I think it answered my question. One thing we had a problem with on our raid the other night was songs over writing.
<br />

<br />
Basically we had 3 bards. My job was to stand with the casters singing resists/CoM/ and a group haste for my rangers (standing by the casters).
<br />

<br />
Bard 2 was sticking with the melee's singing the same thing, rogues in his group for haste.
<br />

<br />
Bard 3 was in the MT group playing CoM, resists, and DS PoV. This caused a few problems. PoV was overwriting the resist song, but our RL was trying to say that there were just too many songs going. 
<br />

<br />
I think I'll let him know that it was just a stacking issue, as we suspected.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
